<p>Rocks are generally split into three categories:</p>
<ol>
  <li>igneous</li>
  <li>metamorphic</li>
  <li>sedimentary</li>
</ol>

<h3>Igneous rocks</h3>
<p><strong>Igneous rocks are formed by the cooling of magma or lava.</strong> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magma">Magma</a> is basically lava underground, and igneous rocks cooled underground can be referred to <em>intrusive</em> rocks. When magma reaches the surface, it's known as lava and rocks which form from lava are known as <em>extrusive</em> (or volcanic) rocks.</p>

